criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. The patient must be minimum 18 years of age;

          2. Diagnosis of angina pectoris as defined by Canadian Cardiovascular Society
             Classification (CCS I, II, III, IV) OR unstable angina pectoris (Braunwald
             Classification B&C, I-II-III) OR patients with documented silent ischemia;

        3 Treatment of one lesion in a native coronary artery. The treated lesion will be the one
        with the highest % diameter stenosis by visual estimate. Additional study stents may be
        used for procedural complications such as dissections. Multivessel treatment is permissible
        in non-target vessels; however, additional lesions may only be treated with commercial
        stents. If other non-target vessels are treated with commercial stents during the index
        procedure, they must be successfully treated prior to the study lesion;

        4. The target lesion is >/=2.0 mm and </=2.5mm in diameter (visual estimate);

        5. The target lesion can be covered with a single 18mm stent;

        6. Target lesion stenosis is >50% and <100% (TIMI I) (visual estimate);

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patient has experienced a Q-wave or non-Q-wave myocardial infarction with documented
             total CK>2 times normal within the preceding 24 hours and the CK and CK-MB enzymes
             remain above normal at the time of treatment;

          2. Target lesion is due to in-stent restenosis;

          3. Ejection fraction 30%;

          4. Totally occluded vessel (TIMI 0 level);

          5. Impaired renal function (creatinine > 3.0 mg/dL);
